values:
To start with some bad news.... I am fishless....
No pets for Sarah... oh well, life will go on.

So I had a really weird dream last night.  How do pople from elementary get into my head?  Really weird.  I dreamt that I was living two lives.  One where I was white trash and another where I was very much not.  What is this dream to mean?    I don't feel as if I'm living two lives, and far from those two too.  And the fact that people from my 1st grade class were in my dream.  What the hell?  Yeah, dreams are weird things.

Ah.... I think i should get doing some wonderful homework...after all i Idon't get it done now.. I can't play.  And is there fun in that?  No, no fun in that.  


Update: Basic Skills test went well, score is not posted yet.  I'm thinking 100% in math?  Writing... 50/50 chance of it being WONDERFUL or that of which we don't speak of.  And finally Reading, Passing score, Got kind of sick of taking a test at that time...But I'm sure it is a passing grade.

I can live with the fact that my parents don't live there anymore.  I may miss the yard, but that will soon pass.  But what I seem to miss the most is thinking that Debbie and I are not going home to the same town!  I worry that her and I will drift apart.  Though I know that Debbie and I will forever be the best of friends.  Hell, we have made it thus far.  
sometimes it is just the simple things we tock for granted.  
Debbie and I use to always plan that we would date twins, and our back yards would conect with a stabel.  -laugh- I don't see that coming true. And for good reasons too.
I just miss Debbie, the yard, and being reminded of the memories that fill that house.  
But as far as lossing my home... home is where ever I shall wonder.

So many things to say...but have no clue where to start.

Isn't it funny how someone's name can mean so much about that person...
Amys are always sucky.  All but one I've ever know that is.  
Should I tell you that one of my room mates name is Amy.  
Stacey's are always the same... fun with their own opinon.  Really, nothing is wrong with that.
Amanda's and I are always the same.  Best of friends almost 24/7.  
What does my name mean to others?  
What do you think of when you think a general Sarah?


I think I am catching a cold.  Amanda and I both that is.  We both have sour throats.  witch doesn't suprise me that we both have one as we have been around each other for the past 5 days stright.  The only time we haven't been around each other is if we are sleeping, bathing, or in 3 out of our 5 classes we don't have together.  No complaints though.  Amanda and I get along well, and respect each other.

My classes are going well thus far.  It has only been 3 days, and I haven't been to my reading class yet.  I have a lot of homework and projects more than in the past.  My goal is to get stright A's.  How wonderful would that be...17 credits of A's added to my GPA.  I would have a 3.3 then!  AWESOME!!

Next weekend I think I'm going to put the books away and have fun.  It'll be the last weekend at the old house, whitch I'm not even sure if I want to go there...  It might be too weird.  But then again it might be a good thing to see for the mental part of everything.  Though I would rather just stay on campus, in one place and enjoy the good ole' college life style.  ;P  

With my luck, I will be helping out the parents; being a slave.  After all isn't that why they had me?

I feel like the string that is holding on by it's last stran, trying to keep things together.  The sad thing is, I am not even a member in this relationship, yet I feel as if I'm their strongest tie left.  They are seeing this, and I will keep pulling them together as long as they are holding on... but this shouldn't really be my job.
I do not get paided enough for all this extra stress....
oh yeah.. I dont' get paided at all right now.
now that sucks

I really wish I had enough time to visit wart lake again this summer.  Every time I stand on that dock my breath is taken away by the view.  I feel as small as an ant yet as huge as a bear. 
I updated my zoto site and there are some photos from my last trip in May.  Take a look; tell me what you think.

My parents have family friends over right now.  Friends from their college days.  Sometimes it seems like they are trying very hard to stay friends.  It makes me wonder are they friends because they enjoy each others company or just because it has become habit.  Another thought it could be because they miss the good ole days.  Is this what we have to look forward to? 

I guess I better get out and have fun now!

:p

Your Birthdate: May 1
Your birthday suggests that are executive ability and leadership qualities in your makeup. A birthday on day 1 of any month gives a measure of will power and self-confidence, and very often a rather original approach. This 1 energy may diminish your ability and desire to handle details, preferring instead to paint with a broad brush. You may be sensitive, but your feelings stay rather repressed.
What Does Your Birth Date Mean?

I'm so excited!  I have twice as many hours with MDI now!!  Betty wanted to kick things up allowing me to absorb as much as I can be for school starts!  The very best part of this that my hours will just be extended so it shouldn't take too much play time!  
Well, off blueberry picking!!!!

always,
Sarah
We have the brick ranch in Jackson!!! yay!
I wish I were there!

fast update!

The ranch house in oakland is still going through some paper work.  Things are ticking.....slowly,..but the bomb will happen sooner or later.  

Life has been on the fast lane around here.  But I still have found time to have some fun!  I went to C.P with Amanda, Becky, Nichole and Justin.  Had a blast!  Photos will be posted soon.

On a sadder note, a family friend's mother passed away this morning.  The battle of cancer was a tuff one.  So please give some prayers for them.

And lastly to end on a happier note, my mom and I are meeting dad down in Jackson to view a few houses.  This should be interesting...weird, maybe fun.  We'll see.  
Sorry so short, more updates on everything later.

Try and keep cool these hot summer days and remember YOU have control of your own feelings and actions.  ;)
keep it real!

Sarah

Your Dominant Thinking Style:

Visioning You are very insightful and tend to make decisions based on your insights. You focus on how things should be - even if you haven't worked out the details. An idealist, thinking of the future helps you guide your path. You tend to give others long-term direction and momentum.

Your Secondary Thinking Style:

Exploring You thrive on the unknown and unpredictable. Novelty is your middle name. You are a challenger. You tend to challenge common assumptions and beliefs. An expert inventor and problem solver, you approach everything from new angles. You show people how to question their models of the world.
What's Your Thinking Style?

</font>

things are going well.... I am really enjoying my room mates and the people around.  They help me forget what I should be doing, and what I don't want to be doing?
....

I don't have any classes tomorrow!!!!
YAY!!!

attempt number two was made....
People try to do things that will make them seem like they are nice.  But all I really ask for is to see if they are listening and caring.  
I found out who was after talking to people tonight.  All I've been talking about is the "bip" and this job i'm applying for.  Yet, only a few of the hand full asked me how I did.  I wonder if some of them even knew that it was today.  Hmm...being dressed up didn't mean anything I'm sure.  speeking of witch I was told seven times that I didn't look like like my self.  Yes! Seven!  The best is when someone says, "Awww Sarah G, I didn't know it was you, you look so nice and pretty today!"  -laughs- good thing I know shes a good friend or i'd wonder....
well i'm out of here
need rest
going home tomorrow
why you ask
to spend time with debbie and get away from room
good night world
good night moon

little kids are to straight forward.  Friday I went to the 2nd grade class I always go to, pre student teaching and a few of the kdis said I didnt look like myself because I was dressed sloopy.  I had a hoody on, and my hair was up.  Nothing that out of the normal for me,but I try to look nice while there.  After all I am an 'adult' there.  The teachers can't look like that, so.  Today, I blew dry my hair and made sure to wear it down.  Just so tehy wouldn't say so.  But...They were to busy telling me my hair was poofy, or it looked like i just woke up.  thanks guys...way to lower my self confidence for the day.
haha jk..
you gota love little kids
oh, and my fav little boy in the class, he wrote on a sticky not for me "I love Sarah"  He has a lot of character, but his teacher doesn't seem to understand his problems.  He is LD, and she knows how to deal with that...hmmm ok.

ok...well hw time.

you know, i think my biggest petpeive are people who don't manage their time and then stress out, complain and begain to hate everything around them.  Oh no, that is my room mate, and the girl known as my best friend here.  shit.  i screwed that one up.  thankfuly we are going away from the xxxx and sarah.  people are learning that there is a sarah g, and i am that.  nice to know.   anyways.....  i could go on and on about how xxxx has been lately.  i could but i'm not going to.  no need to get my boats kicking again.

I was second gussing my actions, so I had my friend read everything.... this is what he got from it.  

[28~02:01] XXXXXXX : Yeah, you jerk. Sarah's the biggest jerk, there is!  Always mean to your XXXXXX and XXXXXXX. I mean why didnt you make them a funny piece of notched wood. or some paper macahe. So, from your point of view he goes out of his way to do simple tasks So it would seem like he always has best intentions towards you.  I know what your saying sarah.  You feel as if you are underappreciated while on the otherhand nothing but hte most extravagant displays of thanks are required for what ( little) is for you?

remember, he has 0% history on any of this...
yet hit the head on the nail
So if it is that noticable why can't others see it?
names have been changed to protect the inacent

OMG!  I'm so glad that only a few people know that I have this site right now!  
So, I'm up late because of this weekend right...My sleeping pattern is really messed up.
I thought I'd be nice to Amanda, and take my computer out in the main room.
Well, I hear things coming from the other room, that I would have rather not heird.  
There is a reason why they like bugs bunny so much.
Do they really think I can't hear them?
URG



p.s.  anyone that reads this and is affended...well think before you act, or moan...

The day after today is filled with mystery...
But just wait for another it'll become history.

Now that I'm back at school things never stop moving.  Mostly things just slow down, and if I'm lucky it isn't because I'm draging my feet.
Campus life is nice.  I love my family, but just living with them is, well a little overwelming.  The stress that was at home does not exist on my sholders anymore.  But my sholders are not weight free, I have classes, and other responabiltys to carry.  But, I don't have anyone but my self to be turn respond to.  Witch makes all the difference.  
Amanda my room mate and Liz the suitmate are cool.  Sara (other suitmate) and I really lucked out.  I am reminded quite often on how lucky I am to have such great room mates, and glad that Sara and I aren't in the same room.  Trust me, it makes a world of a difference.  

Next year, I'm thinking appartment.  Maybe this summer too.  But if that is the path I take, I don't want dad to have to pay for anything besides maybe classes.  I plan on paying him back for these first two years (class/room&bord) too.  Someday...

Well, things will be posted more often.  And maybe I'll get a fun picture up. I miss Bazil and the picture reminds me of one of the few things I miss at home.

I'm really tried, I truly am...but I can't get my self to go to bed.  I've waisted time doing god only knows what.  I see that it is past my bedtime, and know that I have to get up in 5 more hours.  But sleep I can no, no matter how tired I am.

I found out that I'll have my own room next fall, well really I have a room mate ready room.  So does sara.  So it could just be the two of us.  This takes some stress off may back...but adds to it too.  What if they assign someone really soon, who gets the new girl...or do we move in together.  What about carpet, and that sort.  I just don't know.  NOthing ever seems stabel enough for me with the dorms. Or ever...hehe

Spent weekend at Julie and John's.  Henry is a ham as always, and William is a young adolesent "."  Had a very enjoyable weekend.  Went Blueberry picking with the little one. Worked on my crochetting, and learned some new things.  Can't wait till I start my new profect.  

ok...maybe bed isn't looking so bad...

or is it?

euh

who are the one's with probelms?  
us or them?

you know... it never fails, i'm the one people come to.  but I don't mind.  I like helping others.  2 friends came to me tonight with their news.  one out of the blue, the other not as much.  friend one about excitment, she talked to him!  and what dose it mean sarah?!  -laughs- i enjoy trying to find the hidden messages.  Friend two had a problem.  the poor girl...after 2+ years he cheated on her...out of the blue...and with...wow...her.  Friend two and I haven't talked in the last year or more...with going away to school, and changing life styles we sliped away.  Right around the time he started to slip in her life.  But still after all those years,she comes to me.  It takes always be there to another meaning, and I will as always be here for any of my friends.  And with the way guys are these days...I'll always have someone to be here for.

104.3 Oldies has kept me from losing my sane tonight....what is wrong with this picture? 

I cleaned my room today...I mean I changed things around...I mean I washed my walls...and recovered my wallswich plats...I think I need help

Debbie and I were going to go see the village tonight... yeah...but we didn't/arnt.  I understand...she had a long day at work.  But man...I got all dolled up.  And yes, rare for me lately.

....ever notice how you know every song on the oldies stations...

maybe that is why it is entertaining me tonight
